ZH: 他总是随波逐流，从来不做出决定。
EN: He always goes with the flow and never makes decisions.

ZH: 她不愿意随波逐流，选择了自己的道路。
EN: She refuses to go with the flow and chooses her own path.

ZH: 孩子们都随波逐流，跟着大人们走。
EN: The children all go with the flow and follow the adults.

ZH: 在这种情况下，我们能够随波逐流而不受到过多挑战。
EN: In this situation, we can go with the flow without facing too many challenges.

ZH: 有些人随波逐流，其实内心并不愿意。
EN: Some people go with the flow even though they are not willing in their hearts.

ZH: 如果我们都随波逐流，这个团队永远不会进步。
EN: If we all go with the flow, this team will never progress.

ZH: 他不喜欢随波逐流，总是保持独立思考。
EN: He doesn't like going with the flow and always maintains independent thinking.

ZH: 即使别人随波逐流，她也会坚持自己的原则。
EN: Even if others go with the flow, she will stick to her principles.

ZH: 有些人生来就是随波逐流的性格。
EN: Some people are born with a disposition to go with the flow.

ZH: 这个公司成功的秘诀是不随波逐流，勇敢创新。
EN: The key to the success of this company is to not go with the flow, but to innovate bravely.

ZH: 虽然大家都在随波逐流，但是他还是坚持自己的信念。
EN: Although everyone is going with the flow, he still sticks to his beliefs.

ZH: 在这个社会里，随波逐流成为一种普遍现象。
EN: In this society, going with the flow has become a common phenomenon.

ZH: 老板总是不满员工随波逐流，缺乏主见。
EN: The boss is always dissatisfied with employees going with the flow and lacking initiative.

ZH: 在这个竞争激烈的行业里，随波逐流很难赢得成功。
EN: In this competitive industry, it is hard to succeed by going with the flow.

ZH: 他一直在寻找属于自己的方向，不愿意随波逐流。
EN: He has been searching for his own direction and is not willing to go with the flow.

ZH: 许多年轻人受到周围环境的影响，变得随波逐流。
EN: Many young people are influenced by their surroundings and become followers of trends.

ZH: 虽然他们随波逐流，但是至今还没有找到应有的成就感。
EN: Although they go with the flow, they have not yet found a sense of achievement.

ZH: 在这种困难的时刻，不要随波逐流，要坚守信念。
EN: In this difficult moment, don't go with the flow, but stick to your beliefs.

ZH: 他总是随波逐流，找不到自己的价值观。
EN: He always goes with the flow and cannot find his own values.

ZH: 如果你一直随波逐流，很难获得真正的幸福。
EN: If you always go with the flow, it is hard to attain true happiness.
